<h3>The Drusba Dimension</h3>
<p>Brahms’ lullaby was the first sound that struck the ears. It came from the room furthest from the stairs, next to the Martins’ master bedroom, and whispered sweet dreams to the cutest baby seen in millennia. The baby’s name was Baby; what this tells you of her parents’ temperament, I will leave up to your imaginings. Suffice it to say, whatever their attitude toward baby names, their relentless snores were not enough to overtake the peaceful pa-ra-pam-pam pa-ra-pam-pam…</p>
